# Scope: Expo app primary (mobile + web)

As of 2026-07-17 the **primary product** is the Expo app (`mobile/`):

- Native iOS/Android builds
- Web SPA served at the production domain root (via `public/spa` + middleware)

## In scope
- `mobile/` (Expo / React Native / Expo web)
- Shared backend: `app/api/**`, `lib/**` (outside `mobile/`), `supabase/**`
- Domain wiring for Expo web: `proxy.ts`, `scripts/export-expo-web.sh`, `public/spa/` (generated)
- Relocating or maintaining the old Next.js UI under `app/legacy/**` when needed for domain routing

## Out of scope (do not polish)
- New features or visual polish on the **legacy** Next.js website under `/legacy`
- “Parity” work that only improves legacy pages

## Examples
- ❌ Building a new Google Tasks panel only on `app/legacy/tasks/page.tsx`
- ✅ Sync + API under `app/api/**` + UI in `mobile/app/(tabs)/tasks.tsx`
- ✅ Middleware so `myselfapp.xyz/` serves the Expo SPA while `/legacy` keeps the old site

If a request is ambiguous, assume **Expo app** (mobile and/or web SPA). Backend changes are allowed to serve the app.
